rComments: Best professor ever!! Still missing the summer course that I have take with professor!!

Very thoughtful, kind and charitable with his time. If you work hard and do your due diligence, this class will be very rewarding and give you a new understanding of how laws are shaped by economic considerations

The test and exam questions are very general and there are no right/wrong answers. I didn't go to his lectures and got a A. If you skip class then you'll obv. have to read the textbook and go through the lecture slides.   Easy prof. ECO320 with Prof. R. Barber is a must take!
teacherRatingTags: ['Get ready to read', 'Gives good feedback', 'Accessible outside class']

rComments: Took this course and it's more of a theory based course. Be sure you study his power points because the tests are usually based on those main themes. Tests are long but not extremely hard. But you must write your answers in full detail to get full marks.

Most people don't attend his lectures but he's actually a really nice professor. He's very caring and if you have any questions he's happy to help you. His courses aren't too hard but you will still have to study to understand what's going on.

Great prof, tests based off of textbook and slightly supplemented by lecture material. No math in course this year. Always ready to help students and re-explain concepts etc.  Must go to tutorials and do tutorial questions

Barber is  a good easy prof but his lectures can be quite boring (very boring). All he does is basically READ HIS SLIDES WORD FROM WORD in class and draw a few diagrams on the board once in a while.  not a lot of people show up to his lectures (like 20/200 people). Just go to tutorials (many questions in tutorial show up on the test like 75-100%)
Really nice professor. Willing to help when there are questions. Takes his time to explain to you.
